    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good point, but some people argue that even with those measures, the whole concept of high-density zoning is fundamentally flawed because it prioritizes corporate developers and \"growth\" over the actual needs and stability of existing neighborhoods. do you think there's a case to be made that high-density zoning is inherently more destructive to community stability than low-density options?",
