      "content": "High-density zoning is not inherently destructive; it is a tool that can be used to either preserve or destroy communities depending on how it is implemented. The core issue isn't the density itself, but the lack of safeguards like rent control and community benefit agreements that experts have already identified as necessary to prevent displacement. Without these protections, the benefits of density—like reduced sprawl and lower emissions—can easily be overshadowed by the negative social impacts of gentrification.",
